# ContentGuardian environment variables
#
# ALL OPTIONAL for local development. With nothing set, the app runs on local
# SQLite in deterministic MOCK mode (scripted agents + hashed embeddings), so
# `npm install && npm run db:seed && npm run dev` works end-to-end with zero
# external services. See README "Database strategy" and "Architecture decisions".

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LLM provider (optional, both modes)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set a Gemini API key to switch agents + embeddings to live Google Gemini.
# Get one at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=your_key_here

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LOCAL (SQLite) — the default. Leave DATABASE_URL unset.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: override the SQLite database file path (default ./contentguardian.db)
# DATABASE_PATH=./contentguardian.db

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PRODUCTION (Supabase / Postgres). Setting DATABASE_URL switches the app to
# Postgres + pgvector automatically. Use the Supabase TRANSACTION POOLER URL
# (port 6543) at runtime — it is serverless-friendly. prepare:false is applied
# automatically because pgBouncer doesn't support prepared statements.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true
#
# DIRECT (port 5432) connection — used ONLY for running migrations
# (`npm run db:migrate:pg`), which need DDL + non-pooled access.
# DIRECT_URL=postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-0-<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
